*odcctools-20080621 (21 Jun 2008)

  21 Jun 2008; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org>
  +odcctools-20080621.ebuild:
  Version bump, cctools from iPhone SDK Beta 7

  04 May 2008; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org>
  odcctools-20071104.ebuild, odcctools-20080215.ebuild:
  Move the SRC_URI's from pipping's to my homespace, as pipping is definite
  about retiring, so his devspace my disappear sooner or later

*odcctools-20080215 (15 Feb 2008)

  15 Feb 2008; Elias Pipping <pipping@gentoo.org>
  +odcctools-20080215.ebuild:
  bump to ld64-77.1

*odcctools-20071228 (28 Dec 2007)

  28 Dec 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org>
  -odcctools-20071227.ebuild, +odcctools-20071228.ebuild:
  Todays snapshot of odcctools... will this be it?

*odcctools-20071226 (26 Dec 2007)

  26 Dec 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org>
  -odcctools-20071225.ebuild, +odcctools-20071226.ebuild:
  New snapshot with more careful 64-bits patching

*odcctools-20071225 (25 Dec 2007)

  25 Dec 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org>
  -odcctools-20071224.ebuild, +odcctools-20071225.ebuild:
  Replace snapshot with one that compiles on Leopard, still not on Tiger

*odcctools-20071224 (24 Dec 2007)

  24 Dec 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org>
  +odcctools-20071224.ebuild:
  Add new snapshot that fixes a compilation issue in 64-bits mode

  04 Nov 2007; Elias Pipping <pipping@gentoo.org>
  odcctools-20071104.ebuild:
  move ld64 to ld, making ld64 a symling; compile otool now that it works

  18 Oct 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org>
  odcctools-20070629-r1.ebuild:
  Add --program-prefix= to avoid the default of ${CTARGET} when
  cross-compiling. This breaks as what we install does not use the ${CTARGET}

  17 Oct 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org>
  odcctools-20070629-r1.ebuild:
  Made ebuild cross-compile safe, made it work like toolchain-binutils.eclass
  does, so it hopefully once can end up in crossdev.

  15 Oct 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org>
  +files/odcctools-20070629-solaris.patch, odcctools-20070629-r1.ebuild:
  Marked ~x86-solaris and added patch to allow compilation there. For safety
  the patch is only applied when we're not on Darwin

*odcctools-20070629-r1 (10 Oct 2007)

  10 Oct 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org>
  +odcctools-20070629-r1.ebuild:
  Don't install the include files, as they are modified and result in problems
  for packages like tcl

*odcctools-20070629 (30 Jun 2007)

  30 Jun 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org>
  +odcctools-20070629.ebuild:
  New 'snapshot' that fixes build issues with tcl, by building the tar with
  --nosdk. Thanks Elias Pipping for testing this snapshot to be sure it
  doesn't cause trouble

*odcctools-20070412 (12 Apr 2007)

  12 Apr 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org>
  -files/odcctools-20070131-darwin8.8.0.patch, -odcctools-20070131.ebuild,
  +odcctools-20070412.ebuild:
  Bump. Not really new sources, but a new generation of the same sources, with
  the latest DevTools, which makes a difference (patch no longer necessary!)

